        <div class="program-content__section">
          <h2 class="program-content__heading font-display">What It Is</h2>
          <p>AHG's flagship. 8&ndash;12 fellows placed inside legislative offices, policy organizations, and reform institutions where laws get written and power gets exercised.</p>
          <p>Fellows don't observe. They draft policy language, analyze legislation, build coalitions, and produce a capstone reform proposal targeting a real issue in Texas law.</p>
          <p>This is the hardest thing AHG offers. Selection is brutal. The work is harder.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="program-content__section">
          <h2 class="program-content__heading font-display">Selection</h2>
          <p>8&ndash;12 fellows per cohort. We look for demonstrated commitment to reform, sharp analytical thinking, and the spine to hold your ground in rooms that weren't built for you.</p>
          <p>Prior policy experience is not required. Conviction is.</p>
        </div>
