<section class="program-phases">
  <div class="container">
    <h2 class="program-phases__title font-display">The Fellowship</h2>
    <div class="program-phases__timeline">

      <div class="program-phase">
        <span class="program-phase__number font-mono">01</span>
        <div class="program-phase__content">
          <h3 class="program-phase__name font-display">Placement</h3>
          <p>Matched with a legislative office, policy organization, or reform institution based on your issue focus and strengths.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="program-phase">
        <span class="program-phase__number font-mono">02</span>
        <div class="program-phase__content">
          <h3 class="program-phase__name font-display">Policy Curriculum</h3>
          <p>Legislative analysis, policy writing, stakeholder mapping. How a bill moves from draft to floor vote. The plumbing of power.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="program-phase">
        <span class="program-phase__number font-mono">03</span>
        <div class="program-phase__content">
          <h3 class="program-phase__name font-display">Mentor Pairing</h3>
          <p>One-on-one with a senior policy professional, elected official, or legislative staffer. Direct guidance, not a group email.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="program-phase">
        <span class="program-phase__number font-mono">04</span>
        <div class="program-phase__content">
          <h3 class="program-phase__name font-display">Weekly Sessions</h3>
          <p>Cohort working sessions. Present research, debate strategy, sharpen your proposals against peers who will not go easy on you.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="program-phase">
        <span class="program-phase__number font-mono">05</span>
        <div class="program-phase__content">
          <h3 class="program-phase__name font-display">Capstone</h3>
          <p>Every fellow produces a reform proposal&mdash;publication-ready, targeting a specific issue in Texas law or local policy. Built to be used, not filed.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>
  </div>
</section>

